cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the design and implementation of a new oblivious RAM and a history-independent data structure for a key/value map. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the performance of the system, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Amazon Web Services, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
